<li id="cite_note-Moscow_and_the_Peace.2C_Offensive-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Moscow_and_the_Peace.2C_Offensive_4-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.heritage.org/research/russiaandeurasia/bg184.cfm" class="external text" title="http://www.heritage.org/research/russiaandeurasia/bg184.cfm" rel="nofollow">1982 Article "Moscow and the Peace, Offensive"</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-TIME_Magazine-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-TIME_Magazine_5-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/printout/0,8816,960025,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/printout/0,8816,960025,00.html" rel="nofollow">A 1985 <i>Time</i> magazine account of Alexandrov's disappearance</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Mitrokhin-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Mitrokhin_6-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Christopher_Andrew" title="Christopher Andrew">Christopher Andrew</a> and <a href="/wiki/Vasili_Mitrokhin" title="Vasili Mitrokhin">Vasili Mitrokhin</a> (2000). The Mitrokhin Archive: The KGB in Europe and the West. Gardners Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0140284877" class="internal">ISBN 0-14-028487-7</a>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
